query.result:
**English:**
1 The world used to believe, to its peril, 2 that beautiful Venus, the goddess of love, 3 shone in the third sphere of heaven;
4 and so not only did the people of old, in their ancient error, 5 pay her homage with sacrifices and prayers, 6 but they also honored Dione and Cupid,
7 the former as her mother, the latter as her son, 8 and they said that he sat in Dido's lap;
9 and from her, from whom I begin my story, 10 they took the name of the star 11 that the sun now courts, sometimes from above, sometimes from below.
**Old English:**
